#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:1
msgid "Document Composer Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:3
msgid ""
"The Document Composer is a React feature for authoring structured government "
"decision document templates (*beschikkingen*). It follows the same "
"component, storage, and DnD patterns established by the BPMN Modeler and "
"Form Editor."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:7
msgid "Component structure"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:9
msgid ""
"DocumentComposer/\n"
"├── DocumentComposer.tsx       # Root — owns template list state, DnD "
"context, panel layout\n"
"├── DocumentList.tsx           # Left panel — document CRUD and Content "
"library tab\n"
"├── DocumentCanvas.tsx         # Centre panel — zone rendering, block "
"operations, toolbar\n"
"├── ZonePanel.tsx              # Individual zone — droppable container + "
"block list\n"
"├── TextBlockEditor.tsx        # TipTap rich-text block (inline editor)\n"
"├── ImageBlock.tsx             # TriplyDB asset block\n"
"├── VariableBlock.tsx          # Standalone variable-display block\n"
"└── BindingPanel.tsx           # Right panel — {{placeholder}} → variableKey "
"bindings"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:21
msgid ""
"`BpmnModeler/DocumentTemplateSelector.tsx` is injected into the bpmn-js "
"properties panel for `UserTask` elements (separate from the Composer itself)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:25
msgid "Type model"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:27
msgid ""
"Defined in `packages/frontend/src/types/document.types.ts`. Key interfaces:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:29
msgid ""
"interface DocumentTemplate {\n"
"  id: string;\n"
"  name: string;\n"
"  processKey?: string;       // Operaton process definition key\n"
"  serviceId?: string;        // Chain Composer service identifier "
"(informational)\n"
"  schemaVersion: number;     // currently 1\n"
"  zones: DocumentZones;\n"
"  bindings: VariableBinding[];\n"
"  assets: string[];          // TriplyDB asset URLs for dependency tracking\n"
"  createdAt: string;\n"
"  updatedAt: string;\n"
"  readonly?: boolean;\n"
"  status?: 'example' | 'wip';\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"interface DocumentZones {\n"
"  letterhead: DocumentZone;\n"
"  contactInformation: DocumentZone;\n"
"  reference: DocumentZone;\n"
"  body: DocumentZone;\n"
"  closing: DocumentZone;\n"
"  signOff: DocumentZone;\n"
"  annex?: DocumentZone | null;\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"interface DocumentZone {\n"
"  blocks: DocumentBlock[];\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"type BlockType = 'text' | 'image' | 'variable' | 'separator' | 'spacer';\n"
"\n"
"interface DocumentBlock {\n"
"  id: string;\n"
"  type: BlockType;\n"
"  content?: TipTapDoc;       // ProseMirror JSON — for type === 'text'\n"
"  assetUrl?: string;         // for type === 'image'\n"
"  variableKey?: string;      // for type === 'variable'\n"
"  label?: string;\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"interface VariableBinding {\n"
"  id: string;\n"
"  placeholder: string;       // e.g. \"{{permitDecision}}\"\n"
"  variableKey: string;       // Operaton variable name\n"
"  source: 'process' | 'dmn_output';\n"
"  label?: string;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:79
msgid ""
"`ZONE_META` (also in `document.types.ts`) maps each `ZoneId` to a display "
"label, English internal name, required flag, and description. `ZONE_ORDER` "
"defines the fixed rendering sequence (annex always last)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:83
msgid "Storage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:85
msgid ""
"`DocumentService` (`services/documentService.ts`) provides synchronous CRUD "
"over `localStorage`. The storage key is "
"`linkedDataExplorer_documentTemplates`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:87
msgid ""
"DocumentService.getTemplates(): DocumentTemplate[]\n"
"DocumentService.getTemplate(id: string): DocumentTemplate | null\n"
"DocumentService.saveTemplate(template: DocumentTemplate): void\n"
"DocumentService.deleteTemplate(id: string): void"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:96
msgid "Example document seeding"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:98
msgid ""
"The seed document (`Kapvergunning Beschikking`) is stored at `public/"
"examples/flevoland/kapvergunning-beschikking.document` and loaded on first "
"launch via `exampleVersions.ts`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:100
msgid ""
"export const EXAMPLE_VERSIONS: Record<string, number> = {\n"
"  'kapvergunning-beschikking': 1,\n"
"  // ...\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:107
msgid ""
"The app checks `localStorage` key `linkedDataExplorer_exampleVersions`. If "
"the stored version for a key is lower than `EXAMPLE_VERSIONS[key]`, the "
"example file is re-fetched and written (as `readonly: true`, `status: "
"'example'`). This allows updating example content for existing users by "
"incrementing the version number — no `localStorage` clear required."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:109
msgid ""
"**Developer workflow:** edit the example in `public/examples/flevoland/`, "
"mirror the change to `examples/organizations/flevoland/`, increment the "
"version in `exampleVersions.ts`, commit."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:113
msgid "Drag-and-drop"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:115
msgid ""
"Drag-and-drop is implemented with `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable`. "
"The `DndContext` lives in `DocumentComposer.tsx` and passes `dragEndEvent` "
"down to `DocumentCanvas.tsx` via props (to keep business logic in the canvas "
"component while the context wraps the full three-panel layout)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:117
msgid "Two drag types are distinguished via `DragData.type`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:119
msgid ""
"`'new-block'` — dragged from the Content library. Resolved in "
"`DocumentCanvas` by calling `createBlock(dragData)` and appending to the "
"target zone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:120
msgid ""
"`'existing-block'` — dragged from an existing block within a zone. Resolved "
"by either reordering within the zone (`arrayMove`) or moving to a different "
"zone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:122
msgid ""
"Zone droppable IDs use the prefix `zone-{zoneId}` so that `DocumentCanvas` "
"can distinguish a drop onto a zone (append to end) from a drop onto a "
"specific block (insert at position)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:126
msgid "TextBlockEditor and TipTap readonly sync"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:128
msgid ""
"`TextBlockEditor` wraps `@tiptap/react`. TipTap only reads the `editable` "
"option at initialisation and does not react to prop changes. A `useEffect` "
"syncs the `readonly` prop after mount:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:130
msgid ""
"useEffect(() => {\n"
"  editor?.setEditable(!readonly);\n"
"}, [editor, readonly]);"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:136
msgid "This mirrors the pattern in the BPMN Modeler's form editors."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:140
msgid "BindingPanel — variable discovery"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:142
msgid ""
"`BindingPanel` calls `fetchVariableHints(processKey)` from "
"`assetService.ts`, which hits:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:144
msgid "GET /v1/process/:key/variable-hints"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:148
msgid ""
"The backend queries the Operaton history API for all variables present in "
"completed instances of the given process definition key, deduplicates by "
"name, and returns an array of `{ name, type }` objects. The response is "
"typed as `ProcessVariableHint[]`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:152
msgid "DocumentTemplateSelector — BPMN integration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:154
msgid ""
"`DocumentTemplateSelector` (`BpmnModeler/DocumentTemplateSelector.tsx`) is "
"injected into the bpmn-js properties panel alongside `FormTemplateSelector` "
"whenever a `UserTask` is selected. It follows the identical injection "
"pattern (see [BPMN Modeler developer docs]{1}):"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:156
msgid ""
"// BpmnCanvas.tsx — inside selectionChanged, after FormTemplateSelector "
"injection\n"
"if (elementType === 'bpmn:UserTask') {\n"
"  const docRoot = ReactDOM.createRoot(docSelectorContainer);\n"
"  docRoot.render(\n"
"    <DocumentTemplateSelector\n"
"      element={selectedElement}\n"
"      modeling={modeling}\n"
"      selectedDocumentRef={businessObject.get('camunda:documentRef')}\n"
"    />\n"
"  );\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:170
msgid "Selecting a template writes:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:172
msgid ""
"modeling.updateProperties(element, {\n"
"  'camunda:documentRef': templateId,\n"
"});"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:178
msgid ""
"Selecting the blank option sets `camunda:documentRef` to `undefined` "
"(removes the attribute)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:180
msgid "Document badge overlay"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:182
msgid ""
"The purple document badge is rendered in `BpmnCanvas.tsx` in the "
"`element.changed` handler, immediately after the green form badge:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:184
msgid ""
"const documentRef = element.businessObject.get('camunda:documentRef');\n"
"if (documentRef) {\n"
"  overlays.add(element.id, 'document-linked', {\n"
"    position: { bottom: -36, left: leftOffset }, // below the form badge\n"
"    html: `<div class=\"document-linked-badge\" title=\"${documentRef}\">📄 $"
"{documentRef}</div>`,\n"
"  });\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:194
msgid ""
"The badge is positioned 36px below the element (vs. 22px for the form badge)"
", so both badges are visible simultaneously without overlapping."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:198
msgid "Export format"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdocument-composer.md:200
msgid ""
"Clicking **Export .document** serialises the `DocumentTemplate` object to "
"JSON and downloads it with a `.document` extension. The file is identical to "
"what is stored in `localStorage` and can be used as a seed in `public/"
"examples/`."
msgstr ""

